Been feeling some resistance towards things in life & in the world, when a voice in my head delivered this message:

If it’s here, it’s holy.
If it’s happening, it’s holy.

It’s not up to us what “deserves” to be.
It’s just up to us to love it all anyway…

Except for like, the realllllly shitty people/stuff - you know? Always room for growth, sweetie!!💋

Here’s you’re permission slip to go easy on yourself today. You’re enough, you’re doing enough, and you deserve to rest. 

Each day of the week is ruled by a different planet (Saturday = Saturn 🤯).

Mondays are ruled by the gentle, reflective, sensitive Moon. Quite the antithesis of the Monday energy our society has projected onto our psyche.

For most of us, we can’t give away our Monday to pure relaxation, but here’s the invitation to intertwine more of the Moon’s comforting quiet into the first day of the week in what ways we can…

Here are my intentions - 

More tea, less everything else.
This season was made for hot liquids. 

A mental mantra to move slow. 
Followed by a consistent reminder that it is, in fact, okay to move slower. 

Putting down my Instagram for the rest of the day, even though all the AI generated images of my friends are really cool.

Lovingly taking on only the top 3 things on my to do list. 

MOONDAYs are for lovers my fam! And I love you. 🌙

I like to believe that the cultures, music, cuisine, and practices you are drawn to are significant of past life experiences, and Vietnam has always been a place that has called to me. 

That combined with friends who won’t let my joke be JOKES was the perfect recipe for one of the best trips of MUH LIFE! 

When Jimmy and I got engaged, @fromleightoyou asked what I would want to do for a Bachelorette Party... for 2 years I joked that I wanted to go to Vietnam, very well knowing that was “crazy.” 

FLASH FORWARD to a few weeks ago when some of the greatest humans in my life traveled across the globe with me to explore the magical lands of Hanoi, Sa Pa, Hoi An, Ho Chi Minh, etc. 

LOL, we did it! 

I love these girlies with all my heart. Gratitude does not begin to scratch the surface of how I feel about these women in my world. From street Banh Mi sammies multiple times a day.... to food poisoning <3 and all the joys in between, I am filled up on the beauty of friendship and the beauty of this wildly diverse and epic planet we get to share with 8 billion other humans. 

Buy the ticket, take the ride... and thank you to the land of Vietnam for letting this little collection of weirdos explore and delight in your splendour! 

“The only way to know is to find out” -Poonba 

#Vietnam #VietnamTravel #Poonba

I realize traveling is not a personality trait. Yet here I am.

@jimmy.jimes and I went to India and it was an actual dream come true. I have wanted to go to India for as long as I can remember! I bought a wooden frame from World Market 10+ years ago and it came with a black and white image of the Taj Mahal… I never changed the photo because I was in love with it. Now I get to fill it with my own. 

Who knows why we’re pulled to certain places on the planet, but I cried multiple times on our 21 day journey in awe of the most complex country I have ever experienced… and then I cried a couple of times at the sheer intensity of everyday life in India. 

The food, colors, art, architecture, history, music, temples, and nature were as magical as one could imagine, but the people we met along the way wove a texture into our memories that only human connection can provide. And THAT is fkn rad. 

Humans are cool everywhere. And some suck everywhere! But we share this world with people living lives we couldn’t possibly comprehend and that ever-expanding perspective is such a gift that I will not take for granted.

Bahut achchha!

You are SO SPECIAL!

I recently came to the conclusion, while double-chin-doom-scrolling through countless videos and photos of friends and strangers alike, that we all just want to be special. Me included.

I feel like I've been fighting to be special for a long time, to really feel that I'm carrying around some special sauce in my back pocket. But maybe, I don't want to feel that need to be special anymore. And maybe that's what freedom feels like. Or maybe that's giving up?

I've tried to be special in so many ways. Saying things writing things playing things singing things making things sharing things screaming things breaking things. I want to be special because I've seen so many other people be special before me and that makes me think “Well, I should be special too!” Be the snowflake you wish to see in the world, you know? 

We all want to hear the validation confirmation exclamation proclamation appreciation adoration of  -- yes yes yes, you are SPECIAL! You are the MOST special, in fact! You are the top of specialness, peak special, the supreme lord of special, extra extra special. But even if someone tells us we are, in fact, special, can it really be true if we don't believe it for ourselves? And is it actually something worth striving for or is the quest for specialness really just littered with narcissistic delusion? Uhhh, asking for a friend.

So I want to tell you, and me -- that it is actually true -- you are actually a bonafide special human being, made true by the simple fact that you exist (bbboring). And that might not be enough for you, just like it's not enough for me, and that's okay for now, but someday it might be.

I know I run the risk of sounding like a kook with this rant, but I am, and I don't want you to worry about me - I'm in therapy. 

Now tell me I'm special. 

📷 @jill.petracek at @hettybug killer comedy show @1starrevue 

#special #especial
